comments.body:
Makes sense now. I think I understand the main trouble point. I think this is the one:
{quote} unless you only put in non-leaf POMs dependencies that are common to all the leaf modules. {quote}
Today we put any dependency needed by *any* leaf-module in the non-leaf module. That clearly adds a lot of burden on leafs that don't need those libs. Am I understanding that correctly? If so, yeah, let's go for it. At the end of the day, the deps that user sees needs to be as clean as possible.
